							SFDL Language Specification


Simple text.

Text is displayed verbatim. Spaces, CR/LF tabs obeyed as
specified in the text.

TAGS:

<font face=name size=num color=num thpe=bold/italic/underline/sub/super>
Text in between them
</font>

Layers.

Layers are displayed in order they appear in the document.
New layer is shown on top of the previous layer transparently.

TAGS:

<layer>
Items in between the layers.
</layer>


Frames.

Frames are bounding everything included in them.

<frame width=num border=num>
</frame>


Tables.

Tables displayed in row/col dimensions.

Form elements.

List boxes, edit boxes, check boxes, radio buttons.

<list name=text size=num pos=num-x,num-y color=num bgcol=num>
item=text1
item=text2
selected=text1
</list>

<edit>

</edit>


Defaults.

In the beginning of the document, default fonts, colors can be specified.

File Structure.

Simple text

Images.

<img name=text size=num pos=num-x,num-y trans=num>

JPG, GIF, BMP.

Graphic primitives.

Lines, Dots, basic shapes.

<line start=num-x,num-y end=nun-x,num-y color=num
	pattern=text step=num width=num>

<dot pos=num=x,num-y size=num color=num>

<rect p1=coor p2=coor p3=coor p4=coor color=num
	pattern=text step=num width=num fill=text>

<tri p1=num=x,num-y p2=nun-x,num-y p3=num-x,num-y color=num
	pattern=text step=num width=num fill=text>

<circ pos=num =x,num-y end=nun-x,num-y color=num
	pattern=text step=num width=num fill=text>


